# .mailmap — map legacy author/committer emails to GitHub's anonymized form.
#
# Effect: every past commit shown in the GitHub web UI, `git log --use-mailmap`,
# `git shortlog`, and GitHub's contributor graph will display the canonical
# entry (first column) instead of the original (second column).
#
# This does NOT rewrite history. Raw `git log` still shows the original
# emails; the mapping only affects tools that honour .mailmap. That's a
# deliberate trade-off: rewriting 3,080 commits would invalidate every
# existing PR / merge commit / Merkle-2 audit timeline reference.
#
# Format: <canonical-name> <canonical-email> <legacy-email>

# Main author — collapse three personal emails onto the GitHub-noreply form
